Last March, our @eatlearnplay foundation understood that hunger and food insecurity were going to be huge issues for Oakland students and their families when schools closed indefinitely because of the pandemic. More than 18,000 kids in our community depend on school meal programs for multiple meals each day and we made a commitment that they would not go hungry. 15 million meals later, we‚Äôre humbled and inspired by the sheer generosity, tenacity and resilience of our amazing #Oakland community. It‚Äôs been exactly one year since our relief efforts began and while there‚Äôs still a lot of work to do, this feels like an appropriate moment to express our gratitude to the community around us for their incredible support of this work.
